term.description: IV Fluid pressure is too high.
Programed start delay will not be reached.
e.g., "sigh", auto-zero pressure transducer, PRVC "test breath"
Perhaps even more generic: MDCX_QUALITY_LEVEL_; e.g., for QoS levels
Too vendor specific OR should we have a general bag for these enumerations?
A device has identified the need for maintenance (e.g., PM period has expired).
The infusion pump mechanism is stopped.
The infusion pump is programmed to allow patient-initiated drug dosing (e.g., PCA). Replaced pump-mode-pca that has the same value.
The pump is currently priming the fluid line. Though it is moving fluid, it is not intended to be delivered to the patient, but rather to fill the line, purge air, etc.
The pump is programmed in an operational mode that does not match one of the defined modes.
Pump has been powered on or selected and possibly programmed but not "started".
Pump has been programmed and "paused" for an indeterminate period (possibly with configured max period limit).
Pump has been programmed with either a future start time or a delay period after which the infusion will begin.
Pump has been stopped as a result of an alarm condition.
Pump has been stopped by the clinician for a short time after which an alert may signal.
Status when an infusion is complete and not followed by a KVO.
Pump has been programmed and started but is in patient-dose mode or multi-dosing mode and not currently delivering fluid.
The pump is transitioning to a new infusing mode (e.g., piggyback to primary switchover). Used when pump-stopped-delivery-complete is not appropriate.
